Package: breseqConverter
Title: Parse, Compare, and Visualize breseq Mutation Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jae-Yoon", "Sung", email = "sungjaeyoon92@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for analyzing bacterial genome resequencing
    data from breseq. Extracts mutation tables from breseq HTML output, compares
    mutations across multiple evolution stages, classifies mutation types (SNP,
    indel, deletion, etc.), handles circular genome position normalization for
    plasmids, generates publication-ready visualizations, and exports annotated
    GenBank files for viewing in SnapGene. Designed for strain engineering and
    adaptive laboratory evolution (ALE) experiments.
